ions, epitaphs, translations from Latin, Spanish, French, Gaelic and German, and private jeux d’esprit. The comprehensive editorial apparatus provides readers with the historical and literary context for every poem, engages with the relation of song lyrics to musical settings, and traces all "ations and allusions to books, people and places.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aScottish poetryy19th century. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aGarside, P. D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHughes, Gillian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLumsden, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831107804130 cprintz978147442443140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147442444840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474424448423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474424448/original  a978-3-11-078041-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK